ctor-index/flat-index#when-to-use-a-flat-index","content":"Best Practice: Start with Flat Index during development and testing — it’s your reliability anchor. Once you validate your approach, consider approximate indexes (like HNSW) for production-scale performance. Use the Flat index when working with tiny datasets where correctness outweighs speed."},"736":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index-13","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index#advantages","content":"✨ Perfect Recall Guarantee — Finds true nearest neighbors"},"737":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index-14","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index#advantages","content":"✨ Zero Configuration — Simple setup with no tuning required"},"738":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index-15","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index#advantages","content":"✨ Instant Indexing — Build time is virtually immediate"},"739":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index-16","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/flat-index#limitations","content":"⚠️ Search latency grows linearly with dataset size — making it impractical for large-scale workloads."},"740":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/hnsw-index","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/hnsw-index","type":"page","content":"HNSW Index","breadcrumbs":["User Guide","Introduction","Concepts","Vector Index"],"tags":[],"url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/hnsw-index"},"741":{"id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/hnsw-index-0","page_id":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/hnsw-index","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/en/docs/concepts/vector-index/hnsw-index","content":"Hierarchical Navigable Small World"},"742":{"id":"