anges in lighting, pose, or expression, images of one individual generate similar vectors, allowing the system to match identities reliably."],[290,"✅ Rename fields or change their data types ((as long as the change is safe — e.g., from INT32 to INT64)"],[732,"✅ Scenarios where 100% recall is non-negotiable"],[527,"✅ Semantic-Rich: understands context and meaning (e.g., \"king – man + woman ≈ queen\")"],[729,"✅ Small datasets"],[253,"✅ Strengths"],[421,"✅ Text pattern matching:"],[804,"✅ Turn on: When you need higher accuracy  ⚠️ Adds latency due to exact re-scoring"],[849,"✅ You need to tune parameters to achieve optimal performance"],[848,"✅ You’re working with very large datasets and memory efficiency is critical"],[847,"✅ Your vector dataset exhibits natural clustering or locality structure"],[899,"✨ Better scalability on resource-constrained hardware."],[856,"✨ Compatibility — Often used as a base layer in composite indexes (e.g., IVF-PQ) for further optimization"],[768,"✨ Consistently high recall across diverse data distributions"],[78,"✨ Dense + Sparse Vectors: Work with both dense and sparse embeddings, with native support for multi-vector queries in a single call."],[898,"✨ Faster I/O and lower query latency — due to reduced data movement and efficient integer/fp16 arithmetic,"],[769,"✨ Faster indexing than many alternatives (e.g., IVF-based methods)"],[738,"✨ Instant Indexing — Build time is virtually immediate"],[897,"✨ Lower memory footprint — especially when the index is memory-resident,"],[858,"✨ Memory Efficiency — Stores vectors in compact inverted lists with minimal overhead from centroids and list pointers, typically uses significantly less memory than graph-based methods like HNSW"],[767,"✨ Near-logarithmic query time — Typically O(log n) for large datasets"],[736,"✨ Perfect Recall Guarantee — Finds true nearest neighbors"],[857,"✨ Scalability — Query time scales approximately as O(N / n_list × n_probe), making it highly efficient for large N when